File: More than five million coronavirus tests have been conducted in the country. AFP/Pedro Pardo JOHANNESBURG - Coronavirus cases in South Africa have surpassed one million cases, the National Department of Health announced on Sunday. READ: NCCC meets as COVID-19 cases near 1 million The Department reported 9,502 new cases of COVID-19. The total number is now 1,004,413. 214 people have died of COVID-19 taking the total number of deaths to 26,735. 123 of those deaths were recorded in the Eastern Cape. Today, we have breached one million cumulative cases of #COVIDー19 in South Africa, with a cumulative total of 1,004,413 cases reported. pic.twitter.com/4ZlnypuBPl